README as of 15/04/2024 for my tests

BOOTLOADING AND SERIAL MONITORING INSTRUCTIONS

Step 1: PlatformIO CLEAN

Step 2: PlatformIO BUILD

Step 3: PLATFORMIO UPLOAD 
    - Plug in dev board, use device manager to find correct COM port, manually change COM port in platformio.ini (can try auto but didnt work for me)
    - BEFORE pressing UPLOAD, hold down boot button on dev board and press reset then release boot button (ESP32 bootloader mode)
    - Use 115200 baud rate (ESP32 default) 

Step 4: Open PlatformIO SERIAL MONITOR
    - If using older windows, press reset on dev boad once, then press any key on keyboard (keyboard interupt)

N.B.: use ctrl + c to stop serial monitor, then press reset on dev board to restart program and re-enter serial monitor (keyboard interupt)





PYTHON HMI INSTRUCTIONS

Dependencies:
    - matplotlib pyserial (use pip install matplotlib pyserial) 

Step 1: Close the serial monitor in platformio (ctrl + c) and remove terminal window
    - Keep the ESP plugged in 

Step 2: Change COM port in plotting_script.py to match the COM port used in platformio.ini

Step 3: Run plotting_script.py (this should open a matplotlib window to show the live data)